Class AbstractClusterToClusterDivergenceFunction<ClusterType extends Cluster<DataType>,DataType>

  • Type Parameters:
    ClusterType - type of Cluster<DataType> used in the learn() method
    DataType - The algorithm operates on a Collection<DataType>, so DataType will be something like Vector or String
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ClusterToClusterDivergenceFunction<ClusterType,DataType>, DivergenceFunctionContainer<DataType,DataType>, DivergenceFunction<ClusterType,ClusterType>, CloneableSerializable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

public abstract class AbstractClusterToClusterDivergenceFunction<ClusterType extends Cluster<DataType>,DataType>
extends DefaultDivergenceFunctionContainer<DataType,DataType>
implements ClusterToClusterDivergenceFunction<ClusterType,DataType>
    The AbstractClusterToClusterDivergenceFunction class is an abstract class that helps out implementations of ClusterToClusterDivergenceFunction implementations by holding a DivergenceFunction between elements of a cluster.
